description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a suitably qualified, HCPC registered, highly motivated and pro-active Radiographer to take up a full time, permanent Band 6 Radiographer position at the Royal Lancaster Infirmary in the General X-ray Department to join our team who rotate through Nuclear Medicine as part of the General service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in Nuclear Medicine and holding or working towards an appropriate Nuclear Medicine qualification is desirable but not essential as training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Radiology Department carries out a full range of imaging for the Emergency Department, Out-patients, Ward patients, GPs and Theatre work.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You would be expected to cover 7 day working including Bank Holiday cover, as part of a 7 day shift system within the General Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be expected to provide supervision and support to band 5 Radiographers and Students, so leadership skills are essential. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will also be required to support some of the duties delegated by the Lead Radiographers.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
